		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message29970315">Remember that while club comments are pretty relaxed, we expect a higher quality of discussion in the weekly threads, which is why we have guidelines written in the opener for each one. I know it's easy to forget them, and even I tend to forget them at times. Just please reread them once in a while. o (^‿^✿) No worries, there's no problem with some casual posting once in a while, but I just want our new members to not think that's the standard.<br />
<br />
===<br />
<br />
It's been a while since I've seen the series, so I won't be able to fairly describe the positives of the anime as mainly the negatives stuck out over time. I found Code Geass very bad. It required me to suspend my disbelief many times for really big blunders, of which here are some examples:<div class="spoiler"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.nextSibling.nextSibling.style.display='block';this.style.display='none';" value="Show spoiler"> <span class="spoiler_content" style="display:none"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.parentNode.style.display='none';this.parentNode.parentNode.childNodes[0].style.display='block';" value="Hide spoiler"><br>- Lelouch saves the Japanese by having a Britannian representative say they'd grant Zero asylum, and then have all the Japanese cosplay as Zero. The unintentional comedy is strong. They would all have gotten shot thanks to this brilliant plan had it not been for Suzaku conveniently intervening.<br />
- Mao came back to life after being shot dozens/hundred of times because "Britannian medicine is very good" and "Zero ordered his minions to shoot at him, not to kill him".<br />
- On the other hand, Britannian medicine could not save Euphemia from a single wooden bullet.<br />
- When Euphemia was bringing about an early happy end to the series, the writers came up with the single most terrible way to kill her- the Geass randomly activating at the same time as Lelouch saying "I could for example tell you to kill all the Japanese..."<br />
- Notice that this untimely drawback of the Geass was soon removed from the plot (thanks to the lenses) after it served its purpose of killing Euphemia. One wonders why CC didn't give these lenses to Mao, as well.<br />
- Mao isn't the only character coming back to life. It is never explained how in the world Nunnaly survived the bombing. Guilford was seen being caught in the explosion yet reappeared in the final episode. Suzaku was supposedly killed by Kallen in a mecha fight at the end of the series, but he came back with no explanation.<br />
- There is no mention of the Knights of Round in the first season, yet they are main antagonists in the second season.<!--spoiler--></span></div><br />
And here are a few- among many, I think. I'm really focusing on one aspect of the series, but I'd also recommend <!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/blog.php?eid=52936">Baman's article</a> that has a different, more comprehensive approach. I don't agree with everything he says or suggests, but he makes some thought-provoking notes.<br />
<br />
I remember really liking the soundtrack, though. Particularly <!--link--><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P75vosW_Rw8" rel="nofollow">hitomi</a>'s songs. Overall the songs really made for a good atmosphere.</div><div style="margin-top: 8px;"><em>Modified by lpf, 04-12-14, 6:54 AM</em></div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
