		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30055907">A great mindless fun show.<br />
It is, however, not a mindless fun show.<br />
You know what I mean? Yeah, it's a fun show, but I can't consider it good, because it takes itself seriously. It's not an over-the-top nonsense for the sake of entertainment like Hellsing Ultimate or Gurren Lagann, it's a political story with inconsistent tone that keeps going for highschool bullshit, the strategies are far-fetched and rely on the villains being idiots, the worldbuilding doesn't make sense, Suzaku is a hypocrite, and the worst part: R2 reaches a whole new level of asspull fest with Charles' plan, Suzaku's superpowers, magic that pops out of thin air, the Zero Requiem, people were supposed to be dead and are suddenly alive, magical contact lenses, and so on.<br />
<br />
lpf pointed out some plot holes, but there are many more. Why the hell would Lelouch jokingly tell Euphemia to kill all the Japanese? And how much of a coincidence can it be that the Geass evolved at the same time (note: it was never foreshadowed that the Geass could do that)? Why would Lelouch destroy a faction of Japanese that could help his plan and he still pretends to be doing it right? WHY [insert 100 other situations here]?!<br />
<br />
This show a is a joke. Watch it only for mindless over-the-top fun and don't try taking this nonsense seriously like it does to itself.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=35120"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://i.imgur.com/MkmghXm.jpg" /></a></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
