		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30434019">I want to copy and paste Sushi's statement because I couldn't agree more. Code Geass was a blast. I've seen a boatload of anime since then and my opinion of it hasn't changed. It's one of the most fun anime I've had the pleasure of experiencing. I saw it while in high school with my brother and we still talk about from time to time and usually end with "Man, what an entertaining show." I do remember taking the show seriously and I was excited to see what would happen next. I wasn't making fun of it because it was bad. The drama really got me fired up. The ending of both series had me at the edge of my seat. My brother and I said stuff like, "Ohhhhh man, did you see what just happened!?!?!?! That was insane." "Lelouch is such a massive jerk but I love em'!" "Why does Ashford Academy have a slut team!?" It was a wild ride.<br />
<a href="http://lostlink.files.wordpress.com/2008/06/code-geass-12-slut-team.jpg" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><a href="http://lostlink.files.wordpress.com/2008/06/code-geass-12-slut-team.jpg" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://lostlink.files.wordpress.com/2008/06/code-geass-12-slut-team.jpg</a></a><br />
<br />
What's the big deal with being embarrassed at liking Code Geass (or any series for that matter)? Are you not sophisticated if you like something such as this? Is it like saying you don't want to run around in the rain because that's what immature kids do? Are you too adult to enjoy chocolate chip cookies and milk. Hmmmmm!?!? (I just had some today) Hahahaha!</div><div style="margin-top: 8px;"><em>Modified by Nagisa33, 05-01-14, 6:57 PM</em></div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
